rough from submission to acceptance as an Assc. Editor, so feeling very proud. And thanks as always to our reviewers, couldn't do it without you! https://t.co/MgaxXhNUCQ\",\"source\":\"Twitter for Android\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"entities\":{\"annotations\":[{\"start\":67,\"end\":81,\"probability\":0.5003,\"type\":\"Other\",\"normalized_text\":\"Top Paper Award\"}],\"mentions\":[{\"start\":12,\"end\":21,\"username\":\"NothiasT\"},{\"start\":28,\"end\":44,\"username\":\"Journal_Of_Comm\"},{\"start\":57,\"end\":64,\"username\":\"icahdq\"}],\"urls\":[{\"start\":280,\"end\":303,\"url\":\"https://t.co/MgaxXhNUCQ\",\"expanded_url\":\"https://twitter.com/icahdq/status/1399366316360863749\",\"display_url\":\"twitter.com/icahdq/status/…\"}]},\"referenced_tweets\":[{\"type\":\"quoted\",\"id\":\"1399366316360863749\"}],\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":3,\"reply_count\":1,\"like_count\":12,\"quote_count\":1},\"conversation_id\":\"1399722217546604549\",\"created_at\":\"2021-06-01T13:39:16.000Z\",\"id\":\"1399722217546604549\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"825759663933251585\",\"text\":\"@adrishaw @lportwoodstacer I don’t have any hints for making them go except maybe try again? - somehow it worked and I figured out how not to watch the words scrolling across the screen once I decided they were mostly right. I have no idea if anyone else even thought they were a good idea. \\uD83E\\uDD37‍♀️\",\"source\":\"Twitter for iPhone\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"referenced_tweets\":[{\"type\":\"replied_to\",\"id\":\"1399796814941982728\"}],\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":0,\"reply_count\":1,\"like_count\":1,\"quote_count\":0},\"entities\":{\"mentions\":[{\"start\":0,\"end\":9,\"username\":\"adrishaw\"},{\"start\":10,\"end\":26,\"username\":\"lportwoodstacer\"}]},\"conversation_id\":\"1399752101539061761\",\"created_at\":\"2021-06-01T22:46:37.000Z\",\"in_reply_to_user_id\":\"34739420\",\"id\":\"1399859963045072897\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"825759663933251585\",\"text\":\"@adrishaw @lportwoodstacer I don’t know that my recorded talk was really good, but I used the subtitling that comes with PowerPoint to make it more accessible.\",\"source\":\"Twitter for iPhone\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"entities\":{\"annotations\":[{\"start\":121,\"end\":130,\"probability\":0.687,\"type\":\"Product\",\"normalized_text\":\"PowerPoint\"}],\"mentions\":[{\"start\":0,\"end\":9,\"username\":\"adrishaw\"},{\"start\":10,\"end\":26,\"username\":\"lportwoodstacer\"}]},\"referenced_tweets\":[{\"type\":\"replied_to\",\"id\":\"1399752101539061761\"}],\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":0,\"reply_count\":1,\"like_count\":3,\"quote_count\":0},\"conversation_id\":\"1399752101539061761\",\"created_at\":\"2021-06-01T17:23:04.000Z\",\"in_reply_to_user_id\":\"34739420\",\"id\":\"1399778538199343111\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"34739420\",\"text\":\"Crowdsourcing tips from the academic hivemind: what are some tips you have for making really good prerecorded conference presentations? What are some do's/don'ts based on the last year of online conferences you've picked up?\",\"source\":\"Twitter for Android\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":4,\"reply_count\":5,\"like_count\":3,\"quote_count\":1},\"conversation_id\":\"1399752101539061761\",\"created_at\":\"2021-06-01T15:38:01.000Z\",\"id\":\"1399752101539061761\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"31560768\",\"text\":\"Congratulations to all ICA Award Winners, and our sincere gratitude to all the members of the various ICA awards committees, who do tremendous work each year to select each of these recipients: https://t.co/T6KmvKJDUR\",\"source\":\"Hootsuite Inc.\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"entities\":{\"annotations\":[{\"start\":23,\"end\":39,\"probability\":0.431,\"type\":\"Other\",\"normalized_text\":\"ICA Award Winners\"},{\"start\":102,\"end\":104,\"probability\":0.6864,\"type\":\"Organization\",\"normalized_text\":\"ICA\"}],\"urls\":[{\"start\":194,\"end\":217,\"url\":\"https://t.co/T6KmvKJDUR\",\"expanded_url\":\"https://www.icahdq.org/blogpost/1523657/371174/Congratulations-2021-ICA-Award-Winners\",\"display_url\":\"icahdq.org/blogpost/15236…\"}]},\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":5,\"reply_count\":2,\"like_count\":59,\"quote_count\":6},\"conversation_id\":\"1399366316360863749\",\"created_at\":\"2021-05-31T14:05:03.000Z\",\"id\":\"1399366316360863749\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"1366742513751650307\",\"text\":\"#Pride2021 thread! \u2728\\n\\n❤\\uD83E\\uDDE1\\uD83D\\uDC9B\\uD83D\\uDC9A\\uD83D\\uDC99\\uD83D\\uDC9C\\uD83E\\uDD0D\\uD83E\\uDD0E\\uD83D\\uDDA4\\n\\nDid you know @adrishaw created the @LGBTQ_GA? It documents queer games &amp; content across decades, &amp; by type of representation too!\\n\\nLearning about what's been done before is crucial to improve our industry \\n\\nhttps://t.co/FZSjXNs8xE\\n\\n1/∞\",\"source\":\"TweetDeck\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":16,\"reply_count\":1,\"like_count\":21,\"quote_count\":0},\"entities\":{\"mentions\":[{\"start\":46,\"end\":55,\"username\":\"adrishaw\"},{\"start\":68,\"end\":77,\"username\":\"LGBTQ_GA\"}],\"urls\":[{\"start\":248,\"end\":271,\"url\":\"https://t.co/FZSjXNs8xE\",\"expanded_url\":\"https://lgbtqgamearchive.com/\",\"display_url\":\"lgbtqgamearchive.com\",\"images\":[{\"url\":\"https://pbs.twimg.com/news_img/1399680077298810886/0eFDy-N-?format=jpg&name=orig\",\"width\":260,\"height\":260},{\"url\":\"https://pbs.twimg.com/news_img/1399680077298810886/0eFDy-N-?format=jpg&name=150x150\",\"width\":150,\"height\":150}],\"status\":200,\"title\":\"LGBTQ Video Game Archive\",\"description\":\"A curated/researched collection of information of LGBTQ content in digital games from 1980s-present\",\"unwound_url\":\"http://lgbtqgamearchive.com/\"}],\"hashtags\":[{\"start\":0,\"end\":10,\"tag\":\"Pride2021\"}]},\"conversation_id\":\"1399680074950053889\",\"created_at\":\"2021-06-01T10:51:49.000Z\",\"id\":\"1399680074950053889\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"35802340\",\"text\":\"Ok, my last post for #ICA21: ACTUAL FOOTAGE of #ica21danceparty. Music synched up nicely in many places (&amp; yes that IS a gif of @bzelizer). So much gratitude to all of our attendees! See you next year for #ica22 in (we hope, at least partially) Paris! https://t.co/7DX6HQ2RkB\",\"source\":\"Twitter Web App\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"entities\":{\"annotations\":[{\"start\":245,\"end\":249,\"probability\":0.9028,\"type\":\"Place\",\"normalized_text\":\"Paris\"}],\"mentions\":[{\"start\":132,\"end\":141,\"username\":\"bzelizer\"}],\"urls\":[{\"start\":256,\"end\":279,\"url\":\"https://t.co/7DX6HQ2RkB\",\"expanded_url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WnCSQUgmPJE\",\"display_url\":\"youtube.com/watch?v=WnCSQU…\"}],\"hashtags\":[{\"start\":21,\"end\":27,\"tag\":\"ICA21\"},{\"start\":47,\"end\":63,\"tag\":\"ica21danceparty\"},{\"start\":209,\"end\":215,\"tag\":\"ica22\"}]},\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":3,\"reply_count\":2,\"like_count\":16,\"quote_count\":0},\"conversation_id\":\"1399475626009149440\",\"created_at\":\"2021-05-31T21:19:24.000Z\",\"id\":\"1399475626009149440\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"2729615444\",\"text\":\"I’m the first openly LGBTQ person of color to win state office in Pennsylvania.\\n\\nI would be the first gay man and only the 12th Black person to ever serve in the US Senate. \\n\\nWhat barrier will you (yes you) break when you run and win?\",\"source\":\"Twitter for iPhone\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"entities\":{\"annotations\":[{\"start\":66,\"end\":77,\"probability\":0.9984,\"type\":\"Place\",\"normalized_text\":\"Pennsylvania\"},{\"start\":162,\"end\":170,\"probability\":0.6798,\"type\":\"Organization\",\"normalized_text\":\"US Senate\"}]},\"referenced_tweets\":[{\"type\":\"replied_to\",\"id\":\"1399042043171725315\"}],\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":220,\"reply_count\":22,\"like_count\":1429,\"quote_count\":12},\"conversation_id\":\"1399036000249200640\",\"created_at\":\"2021-05-30T16:42:02.000Z\",\"context_annotations\":[{\"domain\":{\"id\":\"88\",\"name\":\"Political Body\",\"description\":\"A section of a government, like The Supreme Court\"},\"entity\":{\"id\":\"961705302700654593\",\"name\":\"United States Congress\",\"description\":\"United States Congress\"}},{\"domain\":{\"id\":\"88\",\"name\":\"Political Body\",\"description\":\"A section of a government, like The Supreme Court\"},\"entity\":{\"id\":\"877326946253684737\",\"name\":\"United States Senate\",\"description\":\"United States Senate\"}},{\"domain\":{\"id\":\"88\",\"name\":\"Political Body\",\"description\":\"A section of a government, like The Supreme Court\"},\"entity\":{\"id\":\"961705302700654593\",\"name\":\"United States Congress\",\"description\":\"United States Congress\"}}],\"in_reply_to_user_id\":\"2729615444\",\"id\":\"1399043434913189905\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"154785018\",\"text\":\"#ica21 Folks, the poster session participants could use some feedback too. The chairs did a nice job, but remember that these are sometimes early career/student participants. Let's try to watch and comment! https://t.co/pSpmhOj2vC\\ncc @ICASECAC\",\"source\":\"TweetDeck\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":2,\"reply_count\":0,\"like_count\":3,\"quote_count\":0},\"entities\":{\"mentions\":[{\"start\":234,\"end\":243,\"username\":\"ICASECAC\"}],\"urls\":[{\"start\":207,\"end\":230,\"url\":\"https://t.co/pSpmhOj2vC\",\"expanded_url\":\"https://ica2021.cadmore.media/Category/38c97938-1e07-4fa7-ab72-51afe9fa70bb\",\"display_url\":\"ica2021.cadmore.media/Category/38c97…\",\"status\":200,\"title\":\"ICA 2021 - 71st Annual ICA Conference Profile Login\",\"unwound_url\":\"https://ica2021.cadmore.media/Profile/Login?returnUrl=https%3a%2f%2fica2021.cadmore.media%2fCategory%2f38c97938-1e07-4fa7-ab72-51afe9fa70bb\"}],\"hashtags\":[{\"start\":0,\"end\":6,\"tag\":\"ica21\"}]},\"conversation_id\":\"1399392548234272775\",\"created_at\":\"2021-05-31T15:49:17.000Z\",\"context_annotations\":[{\"domain\":{\"id\":\"65\",\"name\":\"Interests and Hobbies Vertical\",\"description\":\"Top level interests and hobbies groupings, like Food or Travel\"},\"entity\":{\"id\":\"847544972781826048\",\"name\":\"Careers\",\"description\":\"Careers\"}}],\"id\":\"1399392548234272775\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"19968025\",\"text\":\"\\\"We found a set of files labeled \\\"Computer Conversations,\\\" and the first file folder we opened included a complete source code of ELIZA in MAD-SLIP, with the DOCTOR script!  Here is the real true original ELIZA. You are among the first to see this code in over half a century!\\\" https://t.co/R4kPIehZi9\",\"source\":\"Twitter Web App\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"entities\":{\"annotations\":[{\"start\":130,\"end\":134,\"probability\":0.8633,\"type\":\"Person\",\"normalized_text\":\"ELIZA\"},{\"start\":205,\"end\":209,\"probability\":0.9105,\"type\":\"Person\",\"normalized_text\":\"ELIZA\"}],\"urls\":[{\"start\":278,\"end\":301,\"url\":\"https://t.co/R4kPIehZi9\",\"expanded_url\":\"https://twitter.com/berrydm/status/1398424198054395909\",\"display_url\":\"twitter.com/berrydm/status…\"}]},\"referenced_tweets\":[{\"type\":\"quoted\",\"id\":\"1398424198054395909\"}],\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":59,\"reply_count\":2,\"like_count\":173,\"quote_count\":3},\"conversation_id\":\"1399334914328195073\",\"created_at\":\"2021-05-31T12:00:16.000Z\",\"id\":\"1399334914328195073\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"24075855\",\"text\":\"Bonus points for recognizing that academia is by definition colonial? https://t.co/0xiJCIHaYa\",\"source\":\"Twitter for iPhone\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"referenced_tweets\":[{\"type\":\"quoted\",\"id\":\"1398987182367383552\"}],\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":11,\"reply_count\":3,\"like_count\":73,\"quote_count\":0},\"entities\":{\"urls\":[{\"start\":70,\"end\":93,\"url\":\"https://t.co/0xiJCIHaYa\",\"expanded_url\":\"https://twitter.com/DominicBoyer/status/1398987182367383552\",\"display_url\":\"twitter.com/DominicBoyer/s…\"}]},\"conversation_id\":\"1399200817874444289\",\"created_at\":\"2021-05-31T03:07:25.000Z\",\"id\":\"1399200817874444289\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"14317914\",\"text\":\"Elsevier sponsored “rules of academia” subdivides academics into  three classes: pioneers, settlers and livestock. #openaccess https://t.co/PXUv7spWjX\",\"source\":\"Twitter for iPhone\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"entities\":{\"annotations\":[{\"start\":0,\"end\":7,\"probability\":0.7704,\"type\":\"Organization\",\"normalized_text\":\"Elsevier\"}],\"urls\":[{\"start\":127,\"end\":150,\"url\":\"https://t.co/PXUv7spWjX\",\"expanded_url\":\"https://www.elsevier.com/connect/10-rules-to-survive-in-the-marvellous-but-sinuous-world-of-academia\",\"display_url\":\"elsevier.com/connect/10-rul…\",\"images\":[{\"url\":\"https://pbs.twimg.com/news_img/1405852618195279882/ORj9hWbh?format=jpg&name=orig\",\"width\":1450,\"height\":759},{\"url\":\"https://pbs.twimg.com/news_img/1405852618195279882/ORj9hWbh?format=jpg&name=150x150\",\"width\":150,\"height\":150}],\"status\":200,\"title\":\"10 rules to survive in the marvelous but sinuous world of academia\",\"description\":\"A professor shares the (unwritten) rules he wants PhD students to know before embarking on their academic careers\",\"unwound_url\":\"https://www.elsevier.com/connect/10-rules-to-survive-in-the-marvellous-but-sinuous-world-of-academia\"}],\"hashtags\":[{\"start\":115,\"end\":126,\"tag\":\"openaccess\"}]},\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":96,\"reply_count\":35,\"like_count\":293,\"quote_count\":201},\"conversation_id\":\"1398987182367383552\",\"created_at\":\"2021-05-30T12:58:30.000Z\",\"id\":\"1398987182367383552\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"602142693\",\"text\":\"P.S. If you have had similar experiences with WL and want to be connected to others who have, send me a message with your (non-institutional) email address and I’ll add you to the group. n+1/n\",\"source\":\"Twitter Web App\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"referenced_tweets\":[{\"type\":\"replied_to\",\"id\":\"1398360900541718535\"}],\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":27,\"reply_count\":14,\"like_count\":506,\"quote_count\":0},\"conversation_id\":\"1398360174906068995\",\"created_at\":\"2021-05-28T19:30:31.000Z\",\"in_reply_to_user_id\":\"602142693\",\"id\":\"1398361060881559553\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"602142693\",\"text\":\"4. Finally, consider these invisible burdens in evaluations, admissions, hiring. \\n\\nUnderrepresented people are systematically disadvantaged; we are doing twice as much as you see on our CVs. Our communities won't be healthy until we have equal opportunities to participate. n/n\",\"source\":\"Twitter Web App\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"referenced_tweets\":[{\"type\":\"replied_to\",\"id\":\"1398360814952742912\"}],\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":67,\"reply_count\":3,\"like_count\":763,\"quote_count\":5},\"conversation_id\":\"1398360174906068995\",\"created_at\":\"2021-05-28T19:29:53.000Z\",\"context_annotations\":[{\"domain\":{\"id\":\"45\",\"name\":\"Brand Vertical\",\"description\":\"Top level entities that describe a Brands industry\"},\"entity\":{\"id\":\"781974596706635776\",\"name\":\"Retail\"}},{\"domain\":{\"id\":\"46\",\"name\":\"Brand Category\",\"description\":\"Categories within Brand Verticals that narrow down the scope of Brands\"},\"entity\":{\"id\":\"781974596157251584\",\"name\":\"Grocery/Convenience\"}},{\"domain\":{\"id\":\"47\",\"name\":\"Brand\",\"description\":\"Brands and Companies\"},\"entity\":{\"id\":\"10026799295\",\"name\":\"CVS Pharmacy\"}}],\"in_reply_to_user_id\":\"602142693\",\"id\":\"1398360900541718535\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"602142693\",\"text\":\"3. Be vocal; make it known where you stand. There are others in our community (as well-known and as high-status as WL) whose time isn't up yet, but it will be.\\n\\nAnd support ALL survivors. Harassment and abuse *don't only happen to women*. Not everyone reporting is a woman \\uD83D\\uDC4B 12/n\",\"source\":\"Twitter Web App\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"referenced_tweets\":[{\"type\":\"replied_to\",\"id\":\"1398360688167329793\"}],\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":50,\"reply_count\":4,\"like_count\":729,\"quote_count\":3},\"conversation_id\":\"1398360174906068995\",\"created_at\":\"2021-05-28T19:29:33.000Z\",\"in_reply_to_user_id\":\"602142693\",\"id\":\"1398360814952742912\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"602142693\",\"text\":\"2. Fix the processes in your workplace so they actually do something. The last thing I ever wanted to do was describe where and how WL touched my body to a dozen investigators, colleagues, advisors. No one wants to have to report; make that labor count. 11/n\",\"source\":\"Twitter Web App\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"referenced_tweets\":[{\"type\":\"replied_to\",\"id\":\"1398360656852635653\"}],\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":45,\"reply_count\":1,\"like_count\":639,\"quote_count\":4},\"conversation_id\":\"1398360174906068995\",\"created_at\":\"2021-05-28T19:29:03.000Z\",\"in_reply_to_user_id\":\"602142693\",\"id\":\"1398360688167329793\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"602142693\",\"text\":\"Now what?\\n\\n1. If you've never experienced such abuse, reflect on that privilege—and the fact that, despite what this has cost so many of us, we will still be held (and will perform) to the same standards as you in our careers. This is not equity; this system is unjust. 10/n\",\"source\":\"Twitter Web App\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"referenced_tweets\":[{\"type\":\"replied_to\",\"id\":\"1398360612091039744\"}],\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":69,\"reply_count\":2,\"like_count\":820,\"quote_count\":2},\"conversation_id\":\"1398360174906068995\",\"created_at\":\"2021-05-28T19:28:55.000Z\",\"context_annotations\":[{\"domain\":{\"id\":\"65\",\"name\":\"Interests and Hobbies Vertical\",\"description\":\"Top level interests and hobbies groupings, like Food or Travel\"},\"entity\":{\"id\":\"847544972781826048\",\"name\":\"Careers\",\"description\":\"Careers\"}}],\"in_reply_to_user_id\":\"602142693\",\"id\":\"1398360656852635653\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"602142693\",\"text\":\"So where does this leave us? \\n\\nAs anticipated, I've gained nothing, and the process has cost me time, energy, dignity. \\n\\nWL retains his job and merely \\\"isn't going up for tenure this year\\\"—no word on long-term consequences.\\n\\nStill, at least our community is aware. 9/n\",\"source\":\"Twitter Web App\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"referenced_tweets\":[{\"type\":\"replied_to\",\"id\":\"1398360543526748161\"}],\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":40,\"reply_count\":8,\"like_count\":686,\"quote_count\":3},\"conversation_id\":\"1398360174906068995\",\"created_at\":\"2021-05-28T19:28:44.000Z\",\"in_reply_to_user_id\":\"602142693\",\"id\":\"1398360612091039744\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"602142693\",\"text\":\"3. The consequences range from meaningless to insufficient. @ACM will still allow him in our community after a few years away from conferences, and told us to keep that confidential. @UMichCSE and @UMich say their process concluded correctly. 8/n\",\"source\":\"Twitter Web App\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"referenced_tweets\":[{\"type\":\"replied_to\",\"id\":\"1398360494008795136\"}],\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":33,\"reply_count\":2,\"like_count\":505,\"quote_count\":4},\"entities\":{\"mentions\":[{\"start\":60,\"end\":64,\"username\":\"ACM\"},{\"start\":183,\"end\":192,\"username\":\"UMichCSE\"},{\"start\":197,\"end\":203,\"username\":\"UMich\"}]},\"conversation_id\":\"1398360174906068995\",\"created_at\":\"2021-05-28T19:28:28.000Z\",\"in_reply_to_user_id\":\"602142693\",\"id\":\"1398360543526748161\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"602142693\",\"text\":\"2. The costs were high: For the last year and a half I have spent 5-20 hours/week dealing with this—while finishing a PhD, on the job market, etc. It's taken at least 100 hours (likely more) of my life and  during a critical professional time. 7/n\",\"source\":\"Twitter Web App\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"referenced_tweets\":[{\"type\":\"replied_to\",\"id\":\"1398360448127311874\"}],\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":38,\"reply_count\":3,\"like_count\":677,\"quote_count\":7},\"conversation_id\":\"1398360174906068995\",\"created_at\":\"2021-05-28T19:28:16.000Z\",\"in_reply_to_user_id\":\"602142693\",\"id\":\"1398360494008795136\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"602142693\",\"text\":\"And again, the system failed us: \\n1. The process is rigged for the powerful; his lawyer requested the case be split into 4 individual cases. We were assured this would make no difference, until the finding: there was no evidence of \\\"persistent or pervasive\\\" behavior. 6/n\",\"source\":\"Twitter Web App\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"referenced_tweets\":[{\"type\":\"replied_to\",\"id\":\"1398360371170222081\"}],\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":59,\"reply_count\":1,\"like_count\":603,\"quote_count\":5},\"conversation_id\":\"1398360174906068995\",\"created_at\":\"2021-05-28T19:28:05.000Z\",\"in_reply_to_user_id\":\"602142693\",\"id\":\"1398360448127311874\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"602142693\",\"text\":\"But the realization weighed on me—could I have prevented other abuse? And I was livid that this man, apparently a prolific predator, was enjoying privilege, praise, and access to more people to victimize. \\n\\nWe decided to report. 5/n\",\"source\":\"Twitter Web App\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"referenced_tweets\":[{\"type\":\"replied_to\",\"id\":\"1398360328384040961\"}],\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":27,\"reply_count\":2,\"like_count\":515,\"quote_count\":1},\"conversation_id\":\"1398360174906068995\",\"created_at\":\"2021-05-28T19:27:47.000Z\",\"in_reply_to_user_id\":\"602142693\",\"id\":\"1398360371170222081\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"602142693\",\"text\":\"In 2019, by chance I found out that at least 3 others (probably more) had similar experiences. I was preparing for the academic job market (of course having long decided never to apply to UMich) with nothing to gain personally and a lot to lose. 4/n\",\"source\":\"Twitter Web App\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"referenced_tweets\":[{\"type\":\"replied_to\",\"id\":\"1398360287351173122\"}],\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":21,\"reply_count\":2,\"like_count\":430,\"quote_count\":0},\"conversation_id\":\"1398360174906068995\",\"created_at\":\"2021-05-28T19:27:37.000Z\",\"in_reply_to_user_id\":\"602142693\",\"id\":\"1398360328384040961\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"602142693\",\"text\":\"3. Where could I find support or solidarity? Avoiding him as best I could thereafter, it took me years to learn how many others had similar experiences. 3/n\",\"source\":\"Twitter Web App\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"referenced_tweets\":[{\"type\":\"replied_to\",\"id\":\"1398360227158716416\"}],\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":18,\"reply_count\":2,\"like_count\":446,\"quote_count\":0},\"conversation_id\":\"1398360174906068995\",\"created_at\":\"2021-05-28T19:27:27.000Z\",\"in_reply_to_user_id\":\"602142693\",\"id\":\"1398360287351173122\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"602142693\",\"text\":\"The system failed me then: \\n1. How could this have been avoided? He was well-respected and well-liked; I wasn't tied into whisper networks yet.\\n2. Where to report? It wasn't an official conference event (I wasn't even officially registered) and he knew the hosting faculty. 2/n\",\"source\":\"Twitter Web App\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"referenced_tweets\":[{\"type\":\"replied_to\",\"id\":\"1398360174906068995\"}],\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":27,\"reply_count\":1,\"like_count\":504,\"quote_count\":3},\"conversation_id\":\"1398360174906068995\",\"created_at\":\"2021-05-28T19:27:13.000Z\",\"in_reply_to_user_id\":\"602142693\",\"id\":\"1398360227158716416\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"602142693\",\"text\":\"Since 2016, I have been so careful, so patient, so diligent about the process, but @UMichCSE's statement yesterday—so inadequate as to be insulting—was my final straw.\\n\\nWalter Lasecki sexually harassed me at a CSCW event in 2016; he was a professor &amp; I was a new PhD student. 1/n\",\"source\":\"Twitter Web App\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"entities\":{\"annotations\":[{\"start\":169,\"end\":182,\"probability\":0.9787,\"type\":\"Person\",\"normalized_text\":\"Walter Lasecki\"}],\"mentions\":[{\"start\":83,\"end\":92,\"username\":\"UMichCSE\"}]},\"public_metrics\":{\"retweet_count\":637,\"reply_count\":71,\"like_count\":3903,\"quote_count\":82},\"conversation_id\":\"1398360174906068995\",\"created_at\":\"2021-05-28T19:27:00.000Z\",\"context_annotations\":[{\"domain\":{\"id\":\"65\",\"name\":\"Interests and Hobbies Vertical\",\"description\":\"Top level interests and hobbies groupings, like Food or Travel\"},\"entity\":{\"id\":\"847546154439000064\",\"name\":\"Education\",\"description\":\"Education through the lens of those passionate about resources and news. This topic excludes Education policy and reform.\"}},{\"domain\":{\"id\":\"66\",\"name\":\"Interests and Hobbies Category\",\"description\":\"A grouping of interests and hobbies entities, like Novelty Food or Destinations\"},\"entity\":{\"id\":\"852247095461371904\",\"name\":\"Graduate school\",\"description\":\"Graduate school\"}}],\"id\":\"1398360174906068995\",\"lang\":\"en\"},{\"author_id\":\"35802340\",\"text\":\"#ica21 if you need some perking up or your kids need something to do so they don't bother you while you watch the 3:45pm EDT fellows session, check out the cute activity book @julesmrandolph made for us! Coloring pages, word search, crosswords, mazes, and more! https://t.co/5uFHPZhzIk\",\"source\":\"Twitter Web App\",\"possibly_sensitive\":false,\"attachments\":{\"media_keys\":[\"3_13